<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-01-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-01-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="136" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Presidents Special Assistant</hi>
                                        (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hopkins</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-01-02">January 2,
                                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum for the
                                        President</hi>:</p>
                                <p>Has Bullitt been answered relative to the French fleet,
                                        Alexandria?<note n="1" xml:id="d136fn1">See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_244">p.
                                            244</ref>.</note></p>
                                <p>You will recall that he, in effect, asked for instructions and I
                                    gather <pb facs="0327" n="253" xml:id="pg_253"/> that the joint
                                    view of the British and ourselves is that Bullitt should not
                                    stir that up at the moment.<note n="2" xml:id="d136fn2">See the
                                        discussion at the White House on January 1, 1942, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_153">p.
                                            153</ref>.</note></p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harry L. Hopkins</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>